This paper deals with mathematical frameworks for modelling choice under uncertainty, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper focuses on choice functions and their coherence axioms, which are concepts that are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for decision making and preference modelling. The paper also discusses sets of strict preference orders, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses mathematical concepts such as totality, mixing property, and Archimedeanity, which are related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
